Definition.WordDefinition: Collectible \Col*lect"i*ble\, a. Capable of being collected. [1913 Webster]

collectible adj : subject to or requiring payment especially as specified; "a collectible bill"; "a note payable on demand"; "a check payable to John Doe" [syn: {collectable}, {payable}] n : things considered to be worth collecting (not necessarily valuable or antique) [syn: {collectable}]
